hints_latex:
Note: this hint was giving on the exam itself.

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
Think about the possible remainders when \emph{p} is divided by 6.
\end{description}

statement_latex:
Prove that if \emph{p} is a prime number and \emph{p} \textgreater{} 4,
then

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle
p^2 \equiv 1 \pmod 6
\end{align*}
